p: All females were fed a commercial standard diet (ProPet Puppy Performance 30/22; St. Mary, Ohio) containing minimum 30% of crude protein and minimum 22% of crude fat for at least one week prior to receiving the control diet from Study Days -7 through -1 (acclimation period/ pre-treatment period). Feeding of experimental diets started on Day 1 defined as the day of the first successful mating. From Study Day 1 onward, the control group continued to receive the control diet, while three other groups received food with 0.75%, 1.5% or 3.0% of AOCED ( Table 3).
